===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the oracle bone script, an {{Han compound|虎|人|ls=ic|t1=tiger|t2=person|nocap=1}} — a tiger about to eat a person. Meaning later extended to mean "cruel", "tyrannical".<ref>{{R:yue:Hanzi}}</ref>

===Etymology===
Possibly related to {{och-l|謔|to ridicule}} ({{zh-ref|Bodman, 1980}})。

